iaik.security.mac

Class HMacRipeMd160KeyGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.crypto.KeyGeneratorSpi
      • iaik.security.cipher.VarLengthKeyGenerator
        • iaik.security.mac.HMacRipeMd160KeyGenerator

  • public class HMacRipeMd160KeyGenerator
extends VarLengthKeyGenerator
    This class provides the functionality of KeyGenerator for generating keys to be used by the HmacRipeMd160 MAC algorithm.

    An application uses 

     KeyGenerator keyGen = KeyGenerator.getInstance("HmacRipeMd160");
    for creating a KeyGenerator object for the HmacRipeMd160 algorithm. For actually generating the requested secret key from the KeyGenerator object just created, an application calls the generateKey method after optionally having initialized the generator with some random seed and/or the required key length: 
     SecretKey key = keyGen.generateKey();
    Version:
    File Revision 2
    See Also:
    KeyGenerator, SecretKey, SecretKey, HMacRipeMd160

        public HMacRipeMd160KeyGenerator()
        Creates a new HMAC/RIPEMD-160 key generator. The name for the generated key is HmacRipeMd160, minimum key length 160 bit, no maximum, default key length 512 bit.
